=== Etymology ===
From Middle English ''bere'' from Old English ''bera'' and related to Old English ''brun'' meaning &quot;brown&quot;.

=== Noun ===
'''bear''' (plural: [[bears]])

# A large carnivorous mammal, related to the dog and racoon, having shaggy hair, very small tails and flat feet.<!--does not add to the definition: They like to feed on fruits and insects as well as fish and meat. -->
# An informal name for various animals that resemble a bear, such as a koala or panda.
# (''finance'') An [[investor]] who sells in anticipation of falling prices.
# A problem that is very difficult to solve.
# (''slang'') A large hairy man, especially one who is [[gay]].

